  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Choose two Wizard spells from the Illusion school, each of which must be no higher than level 2, and add them to your spellbook for free.</p><p>In addition, whenever you gain access to a new level of spell slots in this class, you can add one Wizard spell from the Illusion school to your spellbook for free. The chosen spell must be of a level for which you have spell slots.</p><p>You may use a Magic action to change a prepared spell for an Illusion spell in your spellbook. Once you use this feature, you may not do so again until you finish a Long Rest.</p><p>When you reach level 14 in Wizard, you can add your Intelligence modifier (minimum of 1) to any Constitution saving throw you make to maintain Concentration on an Illusion spell.</p>",
